✅ COMPREHENSIVE TAKEAWAYS: SEQUENTIAL INFERENCE WITH PYMDP INTEGRATION
================================================================================
🔍 SEQUENTIAL INFERENCE FOUNDATIONS:
1. Sequential VFE minimization: each update optimally integrates new evidence
2. VFE decomposition: Complexity (belief change) vs Accuracy (model fit)
3. Evidence accumulation tracked through VFE evolution over time
4. Information gain (KL) measures magnitude of belief update at each step
5. Entropy changes reflect whether observations reduce or increase uncertainty
6. Consistent evidence → lower VFE → increased confidence

🚀 PYMDP AGENT INTEGRATION:
7. Agent class performs sophisticated sequential inference over extended time
8. Multi-modal observations accumulate evidence across different channels
9. Temporal patterns emerge from sequential belief updating
10. Context-dependent observations create dynamic inference challenges
11. Belief momentum and stabilization occur through evidence accumulation
12. Extended simulations reveal long-term temporal dynamics

